Patient: How much water should I drink daily with heart failure?
Healthcare Educator: Ideally, limit your fluid intake to 1.5 to 2 liters per day.

Patient: But isn't that too little, won't I get dehydrated?
Healthcare Educator: Your body will adjust. Too much fluid can burden your heart.

Patient: What if I feel really thirsty?
Healthcare Educator: Try rinsing your mouth or sucking on ice cubes. It can help with thirst.

Patient: Can I drink other stuff like soda or juice?
Healthcare Educator: Stick to water. Sugary drinks can lead to weight gain, which can strain your heart.

Patient: Alright, I'll try to follow these suggestions.
Healthcare Educator: Good, remember, small changes can make a big difference for your heart health.